    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with <strong>cling</strong> <strong>film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling</strong> <strong>pin</strong> until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness,</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-kimchi-and-gochujang-chicken-breast-noodle-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> and and cook for 8-9 min, turning once halfway until browned</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-kimchi-and-gochujang-chicken-breast-noodle-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>in half lengthways, then roughly chop</p><p>Peel and slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>cornflour </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[420ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-kimchi-and-gochujang-chicken-breast-noodle-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-kimchi-and-gochujang-chicken-breast-noodle-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped carrot</strong>, <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>chicken stock </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, season with a little <strong>salt </strong>and reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-kimchi-and-gochujang-chicken-breast-noodle-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>medium egg noodles</strong> to a large bowl, cover them with <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and stir for 10 secs to separate the noodles</p><p>Set aside to soak for 5-6 min</p><p>Drain the soaked noodles</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-kimchi-and-gochujang-chicken-breast-noodle-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked through, add your <strong>gochujang paste</strong>, <strong>kimchi ketchup </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>drained noodles</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce is sticky \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy kimchi & gochujang chicken noodle stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-kimchi-and-gochujang-chicken-breast-noodle-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy kimchi & gochujang chicken noodle stew </strong>and chop your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> roughly over the top with scissors</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
